  g) Deploy the Software on public domains, shared infrastructure, or VPS
  h) Allow multiple users or shared access to the Software

Examples of PROHIBITED Commercial Use:
  - Deploying to domain.com or any public domain
  - Running on dev.company.local or internal company networks
  - Hosting on AWS, DigitalOcean, or other cloud providers for others
  - Using to automate tasks for paying clients
  - Including in products or services you sell

Examples of ALLOWED Personal Use:
  - Running on http://localhost:3000 for personal projects
  - Using http://127.0.0.1:PORT for individual automation
